<Window x:Class="SciGit_Client.GettingStarted"
        xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
        xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
        Title="Getting Started" Height="375" Width="550" Icon="/SciGit;component/icon.ico" 
        ResizeMode="NoResize" SnapsToDevicePixels="True">
    <Grid Margin="10" Name="grid">
        <Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
            <ColumnDefinition Width="*" />
        </Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
        <Grid.RowDefinitions>
            <RowDefinition Height="Auto" />
            <RowDefinition Height="*" />
            <RowDefinition Height="Auto" />
            <RowDefinition Height="Auto" />
        </Grid.RowDefinitions>
        
        <TextBlock FontSize="20" Text="Welcome to SciGit!" Margin="0,0,0,10" />
        <StackPanel Name="step1" Grid.Row="1" Margin="0,0,0,10" Visibility="Collapsed">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWithOverflow" LineHeight="16">
                SciGit is an easy way to share and collaborate on documents and papers. <LineBreak />
                You can start by creating <Italic>projects</Italic> that can be shared with collaborators through our website:
                <LineBreak />
                <Button Click="ClickManageProjects" Content="Manage your projects..." Margin="0,10,10,10" /> 
                <Button Click="ClickManageAccount" Content="Manage your account..." Margin="0,10,10,10" />
                <LineBreak />
                You can also join an existing project, or subscribe to a public project.<LineBreak />
                <LineBreak />
                Once added, projects are synced into a local directory (<Hyperlink NavigateUri="http://asdf.com" Name="linkDirectory" RequestNavigate="ClickDirectory" />). <LineBreak />
                Projects appear as subdirectories. You should already have a sample project available - you can try adding files to it, just as you would a regular directory.<LineBreak />
                <LineBreak />
                Changes made to your local project directory can be synced back to SciGit, where your collaborators will also receive your changes.
            </TextBlock>
        </StackPanel>

        <StackPanel Name="step2" Grid.Row="1" Margin="0,0,0,10" Visibility="Collapsed">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWithOverflow" LineHeight="16">
                After you make any changes, a notification in the system tray will prompt you to upload them. <LineBreak />
                Changes will only be uploaded once you manually do so; collaborators will not see your changes until you do this. For example:<LineBreak />
                <LineBreak />
                <Image Source="/SciGit;component/Images/notify_upload.png" Stretch="None" /> <LineBreak />
                <LineBreak />
                A similar notification appears when collaborators have finished uploading their changes. <LineBreak />
                Again, updates to projects are not synced to your local directory until you confirm them.
            </TextBlock>
        </StackPanel>

        <StackPanel Name="step3" Grid.Row="1" Margin="0,0,0,10" Visibility="Collapsed">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWithOverflow" LineHeight="16">
                You can upload, update, or view the history of a project at any time by right-clicking on any file or folder within
                your project directory. <LineBreak />
                <LineBreak />
                <Border BorderBrush="#777" BorderThickness="1">
                    <Image Stretch="None" Source="/SciGit;component/Images/file_contextmenu.png" />
                </Border>
            </TextBlock>
        </StackPanel>

        <DockPanel LastChildFill="True" Name="step4" Grid.Row="1" Margin="0,0,0,10" Visibility="Visible">
            <Border BorderBrush="#777" BorderThickness="1" DockPanel.Dock="Right">
                <Image Stretch="None" Source="/SciGit;component/Images/tray_contextmenu.png" VerticalAlignment="Bottom" />
            </Border>
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWithOverflow" LineHeight="16" Margin="0,0,10,0">
                Alternatively, you can use the tray icon. For convenience, we recommend that you set the icon to stay in the tray area.<LineBreak />
                <LineBreak />
                This concludes the tutorial - you can return here at any time through the tray icon menu. <LineBreak />
                <LineBreak />
                Have fun collaborating, and remember to send any feedback to
                <Hyperlink NavigateUri="mailto:eric@scigit.com" RequestNavigate="HyperlinkNavigate">
                    eric@scigit.com
                </Hyperlink>!
            </TextBlock>
        </DockPanel>

        <Separator Grid.Row="2" Height="1" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" VerticalAlignment="Bottom" Margin="0,0,0,10" />

        <TextBlock Name="status" Grid.Row="3" Text="Step x/y" VerticalAlignment="Center" Foreground="#777" />
        
        <StackPanel Grid.Row="3" Orientation="Horizontal" HorizontalAlignment="Right">
            <Button Name="cancel" Content="Skip" Click="ClickClose" IsCancel="True" Margin="0,0,10,0" />
            <Button Name="prev" Content="&lt; Previous" Click="ClickPrevious" Margin="0,0,10,0" />
            <Button Name="next" Content="Next >" Click="ClickNext" IsDefault="True" />
        </StackPanel>
    </Grid>
</Window>
